==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Post-captain
<hw>Post"-cap`tain</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A captain of a
war vessel whose name appeared, or was ⟦ldquo⟧posted,⟦rdquo⟧ in the
seniority list of the British navy, as distinguished from a commander
whose name was not so posted. The term was also used in the United
States navy; but no such commission as <xex>post-captain</xex> was ever
recognized in either service, and the term has fallen into
disuse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Postcava</ent>⟦br⟧
